    public class DJIInspireCamera
extends DJICamera

    Dji Inspire Camera Class

    Extending the DJICamera class, DJIInspireCamera is specifically designed for M100, Phantom3 Pro and Inspire1. In this class developer could using its APIs for taking photos, recording, setting up the parameter of DJI camera and set up the action while SDK received the system state by invoking API of setDjiCameraSystemStateCallBack.
    You could use this class to modify the parameter settings of photos and recordings so that they could satisfy your requirements. For example, if you want to adjust the size of photo you take, setCameraPhotoSize may help you to do that. With the help of the predefined enums, you could directly set up the parameters.

      • startUpdateTimer

        public boolean startUpdateTimer(int interval)
        Starts the camera's update timer. While the update timer is running, the SDK will request information about the status of the camera from the aircraft, at regular intervals defined by the interval parameter.
        This information is handled through relevant callback interfaces in DJICamera. Not all callbacks handle the update information. Generally, callbacks handling information about camera's state are those that are called according to this update timer.

        Precondition:
        The update timer must not have been started yet, or been stopped with stopUpdateTimer.
        Post Condition:
        The SDK will receive regular information about the state of the camera, allowing developers to monitor the camera's actions. Please note that the interval could not be lower than 100ms.
        Overrides:
        startUpdateTimer in class DJICamera
        Parameters:
        interval - Timer run interval
        See Also:
        DJICamera.startUpdateTimer(int), DJICameraSystemState, DJICameraSDCardInfo, setDjiCameraSystemStateCallBack(DJICameraSystemStateCallBack), setDjiCameraSdcardInfoCallBack(DJICameraSdCardInfoCallBack)

      • stopUpdateTimer

        public boolean stopUpdateTimer()
        Stops the camera's update timer.

        Pre Condition:
        The camera's update timer must first be started with startUpdateTimer.
        Post Condition:
        The SDK will no longer request information from the aircraft about the state of its camera.
        Overrides:
        stopUpdateTimer in class DJICamera
        Returns:

      • onVideoRecv

        public static void onVideoRecv(byte[] videoBuffer,
                               int size)
        Video data update callback. Used with the DJIReceivedVideoDataCallBack, which is called every time the mobile device receives a packet of video data from the aircraft, during live streaming.
        We recommend sending this data to a DjiGLSurfaceView, a widget provided by the SDK to handle video stream data. Use the provided setDataToDecoder function on a DjiGLSurfaceView object to display the video stream on a mobile device.
        H.264, or also called MPEG-4 Part 10, Advanced Video Coding (MPEG-4 AVC) is a video coding format that is currently one of the most commonly used formats for the recording, compression, and distribution of video content.
        Parameters:
        videoBuffer - H.264 video data buffer. Please don't free the buffer after it has been used. The units for the video buffer is bytes.
        size - Size of the video data packet

      • setDjiCameraFileNameInfoCallBack

        public void setDjiCameraFileNameInfoCallBack(DJICameraFileNameInfoCallBack mCameraFileNameInfoCB)
        Supported only by the Phantom 2 Series
        Sets the camera's file information callback.

        Precondition:
        You must first define a DJICameraFileNameInfoCallBack object to pass in as a parameter.

        Post Condition:
        Every time the aircraft's camera captures a photo or a video, the DJICameraFileNameInfoCallback interface that was passed in as a parameter will call its onResult function.
        The onResult function takes in a DJICameraFileNamePushInfo object, which provides the name, path and type of media file that was just captured.
        Overrides:
        setDjiCameraFileNameInfoCallBack in class DJICamera
        Parameters:
        mCameraFileNameInfoCB - The DJICameraFIleNameInfoCallBack object to set as the callback interface every time the aircraft's camera captures a media file.
        The DJICameraFileNameInfoCallback interface implements an onResult function, which takes in a DJICameraFileNamePushInfo object from the aircraft.
        DJICameraFileNamePushInfo contains the name, path and type of the media file that was just captured.
        See Also:
        DJICameraFileNamePushInfo
